Sentencas: In the present work a mesh free method is used to study the effect of interfaces on the crack propagation path in multilayered like Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) materials.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design

Sentencas: The partition of unity principle was introduced to model the crack tip singularity.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design

Sentencas: The penalty method is used to model the materials discontinuity along the interfaces.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design

Sentencas: The stress intensity factors (SIF) were computed using the interaction integral.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design

Sentencas: The mesh free method is implemented and verified using results from the literature.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design

Sentencas: A parametric study of crack propagation in mono-layer and bi-layer material is conducted.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design

Sentencas: Finally an application to SOFC unit shows that crack initiated in the anode propagates towards the anode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Study of interface influence on crack growth: Application to Solid Oxide Fuel Cell like materials design
